a reprogrammable machine (RM) is
- a sequencer (CPU) 
- an array of bytes
- a pointer to a byte - synonymous with an index into the memory array of bytes
- the sequencer sequences through the memory array using a pointer called PC, reads the byte ("opcode") pointed to by PC and uses it to index into a case statement that executes a code snippet specified by the opcode

defbyte - reserve a memory cell (1 byte) and give it a name
defptr  - reserve enough memory cells to index into memory ("pointer") and give it a name